value.title: Mollie Hemingway calls out Kamala Harris' nervous laugh when facing tough questions

value.title: Biden swats cicada off neck before Europe trip: 'Watch out'
value.excerpt: President Biden on Wednesday morning swatted a cicada off his neck ahead of his trip to Europe for the G-7 Summit.

value.title: Biden revokes Trump executive orders targeting TikTok and WeChat
value.excerpt: President Biden has revoked former President Trump’s executive orders that sought to ban downloads of the Chinese-owned apps TikTok and WeChat in the U.S., according to a fact sheet released by the White House Wednesday.

value.title: HUD to reinstate Obama-era fair housing rule gutted under Trump — minus the ‘burdensome’ reporting requirement
value.excerpt: Biden's housing department is restoring the requirement that communities take steps to reduce racial segregation or risk losing federal funds. But missing from the requirement is the 2015 mandate that communities undergo an extensive analysis of local barriers to integration and submit plans to dismantle them to the Department of Housing and Urban Development.

value.title: Ivanka Trump 'focusing on family time' in months after Trump administration
value.excerpt: Ivanka Trump is focusing on her family and living in Miami, Florida, with her husband Jared Kushner, sources familiar with the couple’s plans told Fox News, following four years in Washington, D.C., serving in the Trump administration.

value.title: White House says Harris 'may go to the border' 'at some point'
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris “may go to the border” “at some point,” the White House said Tuesday, as the vice president faces criticism for not yet visiting the southern border after being tappen by President Biden to handle the “root causes” of migration.

value.title: Biden's Justice Department defends Trump in E. Jean Carroll defamation case

value.title: Senate confirms first Biden judicial nominee as Schumer promises to move 'swiftly' on picks
value.excerpt: The Senate Tuesday confirmed the first of President Biden's judicial nominees to a federal district court, starting a long effort for Biden and Senate Democrats to match the massive number of judges confirmed under former President Donald Trump.

value.title: Joe Manchin is opposing big parts of Biden's agenda as the Koch network pressures him
value.excerpt: The Koch network has been actively pressuring Democratic Sen. Joe Manchin to oppose key legislative items linked to Biden's agenda.

value.title: Biden administration threatens Texas with legal action over migrant detention facility closures
value.excerpt: The Biden administration threatened Monday to pursue legal action if Texas Gov. Greg Abbott doesn't rescind his order shutting down federally funded shelters that house migrant children who cross the U.S.-Mexico border without their parents.

value.title: Protesters in Guatemala Meet Kamala Harris With 'Trump Won' Signs
value.excerpt: U.S. Vice President Kamala Harris was met by protesters holding signs reading messages such as "Trump won" and "Go home" in Guatemala on Monday, the New York Post reported, as the country's president blames the Biden administration for this year's migrant crisis.

value.title: Stormy Daniels says she would 'love' to testify in Trump Organization probe
